Step 3: Select language and stack (choose based on anti-bot and ops reality)
There’s no universal “right scraper.” It depends on what Walmart is doing to you today and what you’re willing to pay for stability. The “right” choice is whatever keeps your walmart product data consistent with your requirements and budget.
Quick decision table

• Requests + BeautifulSoup (Python): cheap and fast when the HTML is stable and you are not being challenged; great for lightweight data collection and scrape product jobs where the page data is already in the HTML.

• Playwright or Puppeteer: heavier, but often more reliable when JS rendering is needed or when the site expects browser-like behavior.

• Scrapy: great when you want concurrency, retries, and pipelines, especially for data at scale.
For this run I selected:

• Language: Node.js

• Tech stack: Puppeteer

• Country geotargeting: Any
